Variables I need:

- Indexes to track the position in the two sorted arrays -> i & j.

- An array for the result of merging the two arrays -> merged_array.

Loop:

- A while loop, so that it can keep track of the indexes for each array and increment them separately. 

- The while loop allows you to continue the comparison while both indexes are still inside their arrays.

What happens inside the loop:

- The number at the current index of the first array is compared to the number of the current index of the second array.

- Whichever number is smaller gets added to the merged_array.

- If the number is from nums1 increment i.

- If the number is from nums2 increment j.

What happens after the loop:

- After the main loop is finished that means at least one of the arrays are empty.

- After that, there may be one of them that has leftover numbers. 

- Attach these to the end of the merged_array.

Return:

- Return the merged_array.